'''Jean Michaël Seri''' (born 19 July 1991) is an Ivorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] for [[Slovenian PrvaLiga]] club [[NK Maribor|Maribor]] and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nkmaribor.com/news/VMGYGbYVSStZU58AQ3RA|title=NK Maribor|publisher=NK Maribor|access-date=9 October 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/transfer-jean-micha-l-seri-121500876.html|title=Transfer: Jean-Michaël Seri joins NK Maribor!|first=Foot Africa·1 min|last=read|date=8 September 2025|website=Yahoo Sports|access-date=9 October 2025}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career in the Ivory Coast===
In his native Ivory Coast, the young Seri was nicknamed "Galla", because he tried to emulate the former [[AS Monaco|Monaco]] and [[Paris Saint-Germain]] midfielder [[Marcelo Gallardo]], whose technical skills he admired. Seri joined the Ivorian football academy that was opened in 2001 by the Ivorian footballer [[Cyril Domoraud]]. "Jean is gifted, intelligent and respectful," Domoraud said in retrospect. "In his young days, he was one step ahead of the others, thanks to his ball control."<ref name="JeanSeriESPN5AUg2017">{{cite news|title=Arsenal target Jean Seri destined for big move after Nice displays|url=http://www.espnfc.com/english-premier-league/23/blog/post/3172560/arsenal-target-jean-seri-in-line-for-big-move-after-nice-displays|website=ESPN FC|date=5 August 2017}}</ref>
 
Born in the south-western city of [[Grand-Béréby]], Seri began his career as a youth player with [[Abidjan]] club [[Africa Sports d'Abidjan]] in July 2007.{{citation needed|date=January 2025}} The best clubs in Ivory Coast fought for his services. In January 2010, Seri started his career as a senior player by joining [[ASEC Mimosas]], the most successful club in Ivorian football, where he needed just one season to prove himself and become one of the best players in the country. "He is a great listener, and his state of mind is impeccable," raved Sébastien Desabre, ASEC Mimosas's head coach from October 2010 to October 2012 when Seri was a senior player there, and that quality enabled Seri to make steady progress.<ref name="JeanSeriESPN5AUg2017"/>

===Porto===
On 2 November 2012, Seri joined [[Primeira Liga]] club [[FC Porto|Porto]] on loan, after impressing their scouts. However, there was no place for Seri in the club's first team. He was thus forced to play for the club's [[FC Porto B|reserve team]], scoring once in 19 [[2012–13 Segunda Liga|Segunda Liga]] matches in the first five months of 2013.<ref name="JeanSeriESPN5AUg2017"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/fc-porto/detalhe/dragoes-garantem-jean-michael-seri-786352.html|title=Dragões garantem Jean-Michael Seri|trans-title=Dragons guarantee Jean-Michael Seri|newspaper=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|date=2 November 2012|accessdate=11 March 2014|archive-date=28 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828011049/http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/fc-porto/detalhe/dragoes-garantem-jean-michael-seri-786352.html|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="sw">{{cite news|title=Jean Seri at Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/jean-michael-seri/171726/|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

===Paços de Ferreira===
On 31 August 2013, two months after finishing his loan spell at Porto (the ''Dragões''), Seri joined another [[Primeira Liga]] club [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Paços de Ferreira]] on a permanent basis and on a free transfer by signing a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/fc-porto-jean-michel-seri-assina-pelo-p-ferreira/5221d1f984ae24c6a09fc476.html|title=FC Porto: Jean Michel Seri assina pelo P. Ferreira|trans-title=FC Porto: Jean Michel Seri signs for P. Ferreira|website=MaisFutebol|date=31 August 2013|accessdate=11 March 2014|archivedate=7 June 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140607005735/http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/fc-porto-jean-michel-seri-assina-pelo-p-ferreira/5221d1f984ae24c6a09fc476.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> He debuted for the ''Pacenses'' on 14 September 2013 against [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in a [[2013–14 Primeira Liga|Primeira Liga]] 3–1 away loss.{{citation needed|date=July 2025}} On 2 March 2014, he scored a goal in the 54th minute to register his first competitive goal for Paços de Ferreira in a 3–1 Primeira Liga home win over [[C.S. Marítimo|Marítimo]] to send his side away from the relegation zone.{{citation needed|date=July 2025}} It was at Paços de Ferreira where Seri's magnificent range of passing and ability to dictate the tempo of the game made him a fans' favourite. The club finished in eighth place in the [[2014–15 Primeira Liga]], and [[Ligue 1]] club [[OGC Nice|Nice]] were quick to sign Seri before bigger clubs took notice.<ref name="JeanSeriESPN5AUg2017"/>

===Nice===
[[File:Loc-Nicca (14).jpg|thumb|upright|Seri playing for Nice against [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow]] in 2018]]

On 11 June 2015, Seri officially joined [[Ligue 1]] club [[OGC Nice|Nice]] for a transfer fee of €1 million.<ref name="JeanSeriESPN5AUg2017"/><ref>{{cite news|title=Seri à Nice, c'est officiel|trans-title=Seri to Nice, it's official|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Seri-a-nice-c-est-officiel/565777|accessdate=19 February 2017|newspaper=L'Equipe|date=11 June 2015|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Jean-Michaël Seri : L'Ivoirien signe à Nice|trans-title=Jean-Michaël Seri: The Ivorian signs to Nice|url=http://www.africatopsports.com/2015/06/11/jean-michael-seri-livoirien-signe-a-nice/|website=Africa Top Sports|accessdate=19 February 2017|language=fr|date=11 June 2015}}</ref> On 27 May 2015, prior to the opening of the transfer window, the club had announced the "very likely" arrival of Seri.<ref>{{cite news|title=P. Ferreira: Nice confirma contratação de Seri|trans-title=P. Ferreira: Nice confirms Seri signing|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/transferencias/pacos-ferreira/p-ferreira-nice-confirma-contratacao-de-seri|accessdate=19 February 2017|website=MaisFutebol|date=27 May 2015|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Jean-Michael Seri arrive aussi|trans-title=Jean-Michael Seri also arrives|url=http://www.ogcnice.com/fr/actualite/23944/jean-michael-seri-arrive-aussi|publisher=OGC Nice|accessdate=19 February 2017|language=fr}}</ref> On 8 August 2015, Seri made his competitive debut for Nice in their opening match of the [[2015–16 Ligue 1]] season, playing the entire match in the 2–1 home loss to [[AS Monaco|Monaco]]. On 27 September 2015, he scored in the 53rd minute to register his first competitive goal for Nice in a 4–1 Ligue 1 away win over [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]].<ref name="sw"/>

===Fulham===
In July 2018, Seri joined [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] on a four-year deal until 2022 with an option for Fulham to extend the contract by a further year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jean Michael Seri: Fulham sign Ivory Coast international from Nice |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44807027 |accessdate=12 July 2018 |website=BBC Sport |date=12 July 2018}}</ref>

Seri scored his first goal for his new club on 26 August, opening the scoring against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] with a spectacular strike from outside the area. Seri picked the ball up and took one touch around an oncoming defender before curling in a long-range effort into the top corner of [[Joe Hart]]'s net and the goal was awarded with the [[Premier League Goal of the Month]] for August.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/845186|title=Seri strike wins Carling Goal of the Month for August 2018|publisher=Premier League|date=7 September 2018|accessdate=21 January 2020}}</ref>

====Loan to Galatasaray====
On 18 July 2019, Seri joined [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] on a season-long loan deal, with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Loan deal for Seri |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44807027 |accessdate=19 July 2019 |work=BBC Sport|date=18 July 2019}}</ref> Eventually, he would leave Galatasaray and return to Fulham at the end of the season.

====Loan to Bordeaux====
On 30 January 2021, Seri joined Ligue 1 club [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]] on loan until the end of the [[2020–21 FC Girondins de Bordeaux season|season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2021/january/Seri-Joins-Bordeaux/ |title=Seri joins Bordeaux |publisher=Fulham FC |date=30 January 2021 |accessdate=30 January 2021}}</ref>

====Return to Fulham====
Following his return from his loan spell at [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]], Seri began playing again for [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] starting his first match for the club for the season against [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]], which saw Fulham win 5–1 in the [[2021–22 EFL Championship|Championship]] on 14 August 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58124645|title=Huddersfield Town 1–5 Fulham|website=BBC Sport|date=14 August 2021|accessdate=17 September 2021}}</ref> On 2 May 2022, Seri both featured and scored in a 7–0 victory over [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]], this victory securing the Championship title for Fulham.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/61212426|title=Fulham 7–0 Luton Town: Fulham clinch Championship title with emphatic Luton victory|work=BBC Sport|date=2 May 2022|accessdate=8 July 2022}}</ref> Despite promotion back to the Premier League, it was announced that Seri would be leaving the club at the end of his contract in June 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2022/may/23/player-departures/|title=Player Departures|website=www.fulhamfc.com|date=23 May 2022|accessdate=8 July 2022}}</ref>

===Hull City===
Seri returned to the Championship on 8 July 2022 to join [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] on a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wearehullcity.co.uk/news/2022/july/seri-signs-for-hull-city/|title=Seri signs for Hull City|website=www.wearehullcity.co.uk|date=8 July 2022|accessdate=8 July 2022}}</ref> On 30 July 2022, he would mark his debut with the winning goal in a 2–1 home victory over [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]].<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62274831 | title = Hull City 2–1 Bristol City | date = 30 July 2022 | work = BBC Sport | accessdate = 30 July 2022}}</ref> His next goal for the Tigers would come on 10 April 2024, scoring his side's second goal in a 2–2 draw with [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]].<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/68719945 | title = Hull City 2–2 Middlesbrough | date = 10 April 2024 | work = BBC Sport | accessdate = 25 July 2024}}</ref>

===Al-Orobah===
On 23 August 2024, Seri signed for newly promoted [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al-Orobah FC|Al-Orobah]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wearehullcity.co.uk/news/2024/august/23/seri-signs-for-al-orobah/|title=Seri signs for Al-Orobah|website=www.wearehullcity.co.uk|date=23 August 2024|accessdate=23 August 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Seri made a total of three appearances for the [[Ivory Coast national under-23 football team|Ivory Coast under-23 team]], all of them at the [[2011 CAF U-23 Championship]] held in Morocco, playing every minute of all their three Group B matches against South Africa, Egypt and Gabon. Ivory Coast finished third in Group B and thus did not qualify for the semifinals.

On 27 February 2014, Seri received his first senior international call up for the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]] in an upcoming [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]];<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/Futebol/Nacional/1a_liga/pacos_ferreira/interior.aspx?content_id=870292 |title=Séri convocado para a seleção costa-marfinense |trans-title=Séri selected for the Ivorians |newspaper=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]] |date=27 February 2014 |accessdate=11 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140305182620/http://www.record.xl.pt/Futebol/Nacional/1a_liga/pacos_ferreira/interior.aspx?content_id=870292 |archivedate= 5 March 2014 }}</ref> he was an unused substitute in ''The Elephants''' 2–2 away draw (held on 5 March 2014) against Belgium.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2014/03/05/4867900/belgium-draws-with-ivory-coast.html|title=Belgium draws with Ivory Coast 2–2 in WCup warm-up|website=KansasCitySports|date=5 March 2014|accessdate=11 March 2014}}</ref> On 6 September 2015, Seri made his senior international debut in a [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group I|2017 Africa Cup of Nations qualification match]] against [[Sierra Leone national football team|Sierra Leone]], playing the entire match in the 0–0 away draw. On 17 November 2015, Seri scored a goal in the 64th minute of the [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF second round|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]] second round second leg 3–0 home win over [[Liberia national football team|Liberia]] to register his first senior international goal.

Seri played two of Ivory Coast's three [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations]] Group C matches as they finished third in Group C and thus did not qualify for the quarter-finals. In the [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations|2019 edition]] of the tournament he also made two group stage appearances, starting against [[South Africa national football team|South Africa]] and [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/team/squad/_/id/4789/league/CAF.NATIONS/season/2019|title=Ivory Coast Squad|accessdate=16 January 2024|website=ESPN}}</ref>

Seri was a member of the Ivory Coast's squad for the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]] and started in all four of the team's matches as they reached the round of 16, losing 5–4 to [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]] in a [[penalty shootout]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/team/squad/_/id/4789/league/CAF.NATIONS/season/2021|title=Ivory Coast Squad|accessdate=16 January 2024|website=ESPN}}</ref>

In December 2023, Seri was named in the Ivory Coast's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]], and ended up winning the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/federationivoiriennedefootball/posts/pfbid02GVkTYXjhv2yBQizHRNxngTGoMrFLXgcUg3kQeXgEk3gZ158w6cxqRFjDBXCCU3ihl|title=LA LISTE|publisher=[[Ivorian Football Federation]]|date=28 December 2023|accessdate=16 January 2024|language=pt|via=[[Facebook]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.7info.ci/cote-divoire-voici-les-27-elephants-de-gasset-zaha-et-des-tenors-font-leurs-adieux-a-la-can-2023/|title=Côte d'Ivoire: voici les 27 Eléphants de Gasset, Zaha et des ténors font leurs adieux à la CAN 2023|publisher=[[7info]]|first=Tristan|last=Sahi|date=28 December 2023|accessdate=16 January 2024|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/media/ow2obxrw/c%C3%B4te-divoire.pdf|title=CÔTE D'IVOIRE|publisher=Confederation of African Football|date=5 January 2024}}</ref>

On May 15, 2026, Seri was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Faé]] in his list of 26 players in order to participate in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

==Personal life==
Seri is a devout [[Christianity|Christian]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Jean Michaël Seri: 'You have to take risks or you are just a water carrier'|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/oct/06/jean-michael-seri-risks-water-carrier-fulham-barcelona|date=6 October 2018|accessdate=6 January 2019|newspaper=The Guardian |first=Dominic|last=Field}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Fulham star reveals why he snubbed Chelsea, Spurs and Liverpool to join The Cottagers|url=https://www.xtheline.co.uk/fulham-star-reveals-why-he-snubbed-chelsea-spurs-and-liverpool-to-join-the-cottagers/|date=5 September 2018|accessdate=6 January 2019|website=X The Line|first=Ollie|last=Baines|archivedate=13 April 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190413220605/https://www.xtheline.co.uk/fulham-star-reveals-why-he-snubbed-chelsea-spurs-and-liverpool-to-join-the-cottagers/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

